text: Overpriced Indian Muslim Stall (Al Zara) charges $8 for a Nasi Goreng Ayam. If this was at Orchard Road, I would be ok with the price. But no, this store is located in the an industrial area. When I asked him about the price, he says its the normal price for a plate of Nasi Goreng Ayam. I dont know who is he trying to scam because the average pricing is around $5-$6. Do not patronise this stall.
One of the best places to have indian breakfast and lunch in the west. Very rare to find such good cooks in indian dishes near your workplace especially this far out in the west side of Singapore.
A good place to rest and go...varieties of stall.
The Indian stall is not bad
Nasi lemak $4, coffee $1.50. Shouldn't it be cheaper since it's in an industrial estate?
